			This paper gives an overview of the NAACL-2010 Workshop on Creating Speech and Language DataWith Amazon?s Mechanical Turk.
			A number of recent papers have evaluated the effectiveness of us ing Mechanical Turk to create annotated data for natural language processing applications.
			The lowcost, scalable workforce available through Mechan ical Turk (MTurk) and other crowdsourcing sites opens new possibilities for annotating speech and text, and has the potential to dramatically changehow we create data for human language technolo gies.
